{{about|the puppetry association|other uses|}} [[Image:LA MAISON DES MARIONETTES CHARLEVILLE MEZIERS.jpg|thumb|The seat of UNIMA in Charleville-Mézières, France]] [[Image:Marionette Union.jpg|thumb|270px|Memorial tablet commemorating the founding of UNIMA in Prague, Czech Republic]] '''UNIMA''' (''Union Internationale de la Marionnette'' - ''International Puppetry Association'') was founded in [[Prague]] in 1929 (the then Czechoslovak magazine [[Loutkář]] was UNIMA's first official journal in years 1929-1930). In 1981, the French puppeteer Jacques Félix moved UNIMA's headquarters to [[Charleville-Mézières]], [[France]], location of the ''Festival Mondial des Théâtres de Marionnettes'' since 1972. UNIMA is affiliated to [[UNESCO]] and it is a member of the [[International Theatre Institute]].
== National centers == [[Image:Levy-Trudeau-Katz.jpg|thumb|350px|UNIMA Festival, Armenia 2015 (Right to Left): Martine Levy ([[UNESCO]]); Jacques Trudeau (Secretary General of UNIMA); Dikla Katz ([[The Key Theatre]], UNIMA Representative in [[Israel]])]] There are National centers throughout the world,<ref>{{Cite web| title = News from National centers | accessdate = 2009-04-03| url = http://pagesperso-orange.fr/unima/uniE131.htm}}</ref> which include: * [[UNIMA-USA]] founded by [[Jim Henson]] in 1966. In 1992 the [[Center for Puppetry Arts]] in Atlanta became the headquarters for UNIMA-USA * [[UNIMA Australia]] * [[Theatre of Pakistan#UNIMA Pakistan|UNIMA Pakistan]] * British UNIMA * UNIMA France - [[:fr:THEMAA|THEMAA]]
